HEADWORD: Unconcern
<hw>Un`con*cern"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Want of concern;
absence of anxiety; freedom from solicitude; indifference.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A listless <qex>unconcern</qex>,⟦br⟧
Cold, and averting from our neighbor's good.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unconcerned</ent>⟦br⟧
